. * ── Method 1: Naive Difference in Means ──────────────────────────────────
. 
. display _newline(1)



. display "--- Method 1: Naive Difference in Means ---"
--- Method 1: Naive Difference in Means ---

. 
. ttest re78, by(treat)

Two-sample t test with equal variances
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Group |     Obs        Mean    Std. err.   Std. dev.   [95% conf. interval]
---------+--------------------------------------------------------------------
       0 |     260    4554.801    340.0931    5483.836    3885.102    5224.501
       1 |     185    6349.144    578.4229    7867.402    5207.949    7490.338
---------+--------------------------------------------------------------------
Combined |     445    5300.764    314.3629    6631.492     4682.94    5918.588
---------+--------------------------------------------------------------------
    diff |           -1794.342    632.8534                -3038.11   -550.5745
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    diff = mean(0) - mean(1)                                      t =  -2.8353
H0: diff = 0                                     Degrees of freedom =      443

    Ha: diff < 0                 Ha: diff != 0                 Ha: diff > 0
 Pr(T < t) = 0.0024         Pr(|T| > |t|) = 0.0048          Pr(T > t) = 0.9976

. 
. * Store the ATE (treat=1 mean minus treat=0 mean)
. summarize re78 if treat == 1

    Variable |        Obs        Mean    Std. dev.       Min        Max
-------------+---------------------------------------------------------
        re78 |        185    6349.144    7867.402          0   60307.93

. scalar mean_treated = r(mean)

. summarize re78 if treat == 0

    Variable |        Obs        Mean    Std. dev.       Min        Max
-------------+---------------------------------------------------------
        re78 |        260    4554.801    5483.836          0   39483.53

. scalar mean_control = r(mean)

. scalar naive_ate = mean_treated - mean_control

